Reasoning: 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely category as the paper presents a framework of dynamic compressed data structures for string manipulation. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is also likely as the paper discusses theoretical bounds for the resources used by the structures. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a possibility as the paper mentions searchable partial sums and FM-indexes, which are commonly used in text retrieval. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a possibility as the paper discusses the efficiency of compression algorithms. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a possibility as the paper presents an open-source C++ library.
